    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sorsby</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Paz, Bolivia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 185.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm the receipt of your
                    sad message of the 1st instant, and to say that I immediately notified the
                    government, which as an expression of sympathy displayed the government flag at
                    half-mast on all government buildings, and that the flag of this legation was
                    displayed at half-mast on the 2d, 3d, and 4th, as a symbol of mourning.</p>
                <p>The expression of condolence by the government and officials by the foreign
                    representatives, as well as others of prominence here, has been general and
                    genuine, and, personally, I have the honor to request that my most profound
                    sympathy in this great loss to the country be conveyed to the President.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William B. Sorsby.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
